  "feedback": "## ATX Review — Iteration 3 (Issue #820)\n\n**Rating: 4 / 5**\n**Specialists invoked:** render-engine, security-reviewer, test-coverage\n**Prior blockers status:** All resolved ✅\n\n---\n\n### Review-1 \u0026 Review-2 Blocker Closure\n\n| Blocker | Description | Status |\n|---------|-------------|--------|\n| R1-B1 | Dict auth crashes `_clean_secret` with `AttributeError` | ✅ Fixed — dict unwrapped to bare string before `_clean_secret` |\n| R1-B2 | Missing `token` key silently produces empty bearer | ✅ Fixed — raises `AgentConfigError` |\n| R2-B1 | Whitespace-only dict token bypasses validation | ✅ Fixed — `not token.strip()` rejects `\"   \"`, `\"\\t\\n\"` |\n| R2-B2 | Whitespace-only bare-string auth emits no-auth gateway | ✅ Fixed — `.strip()` after `_clean_secret` collapses to empty |\n\n### Warnings\n\n| # | Location | Issue |\n|---|----------|-------|\n| W1 | `render.py:608` | **NUL-only dict token bypass.** `str.strip()` does not remove NUL (`\\x00`), so `{\"mode\": \"token\", \"token\": \"\\x00\"}` passes the `not token.strip()` guard as truthy, then `_clean_secret` strips the NUL → empty string → no-auth gateway. Same failure class as R2-B1 but for NUL instead of whitespace. Fix: validate the cleaned form — `cleaned = _clean_secret(token).strip(); if not cleaned: raise`. Low probability in practice (NUL-only tokens in hosts.json require deliberate injection), but inconsistent with the strict validation applied to whitespace-only tokens. |\n| W2 | `render.py:631` + `test_render.py:1433` | **Asymmetric whitespace handling.** Dict-shape whitespace-only token raises `AgentConfigError`; bare-string whitespace-only auth silently collapses to `\"\"` and produces a config with no auth block. Both represent the same operator failure (corrupted bearer), but the bare-string path silently degrades instead of failing loudly. Under the #437 invariant (\"every lifecycle op mints a fresh bearer\"), an empty bearer at render time signals rotation didn't run or wrote garbage — raising would be the safer choice. The current behavior is explicitly tested and documented, so this is a design-level warning, not a code bug. |\n| W3 | `test_render.py:1371-1372` | **Substring JSON assertions are brittle.** `assert '\"token\": \"{expected_token}\"' in json_body` matches anywhere in the document, not at the `gateway.auth.token` path specifically. Replace with `json.loads(json_body)[\"gateway\"][\"auth\"][\"token\"]` for structural precision. No false-positive risk today, but fragile against future baseline changes. |\n\n### Suggestions\n\n| # | Location | Suggestion |\n|---|----------|------------|\n| S1 | `render.py:631` | Extract a `_clean_and_strip(value)` helper combining `_clean_secret` + `.strip()` to reduce copy-paste risk for future secret fields. |\n| S2 | `test_render.py:1480` | Strengthen zeroclaw render assertion: parse the TOML with `tomllib.loads()` to confirm a dict-leaking into a string context would break the parser, rather than just checking key existence. |\n| S3 | `render.py:595-617` | Optional: note that extra keys in the dict shape (beyond `mode` + `token`) are intentionally permitted for forward compatibility. |\n\n### Test Coverage Assessment\n\nAll review-2 items confirmed covered:\n- **W1** (zeroclaw): `test_gateway_auth_dict_shape_works_for_zeroclaw` ✅\n- **W2** (whitespace cases): `\"   \"` and `\"\\t\\n\"` in parametrized rejection tests + `test_gateway_auth_bare_string_whitespace_becomes_empty` ✅\n- **Byte-identical equivalence**: `test_gateway_auth_byte_identical_across_string_and_dict_shapes` ✅\n- **NUL-in-real-token**: Covered by acceptance parametrize (`_AUTH_TOKEN_820 + \"\\x00tail\"`) ✅\n- **Gap**: NUL-only dict token (`\"\\x00\"`, `\"\\x00   \"`) not tested — related to W1 above.\n\n### Verdict\n\nThe core fix is sound. All four prior blockers are confirmed closed. The dict-unwrap → `_clean_secret` → `.strip()` pipeline correctly normalizes both shapes at the assembly boundary, and the validation catches the realistic malformed inputs (wrong mode, missing token, empty token, whitespace-only token, wrong types). The NUL-only dict token gap (W1) is a low-probability edge that should be closed in a follow-up hardening pass but does not block merge. Rating: **4/5**, no blockers.",
