      "result": "\u003coutput\u003e\n{\n  \"rating\": 4,\n  \"summary\": \"All four prior blockers are resolved. The dict-unwrap at lines 595-617 correctly validates mode=='token', rejects missing/empty/whitespace-only tokens via `not token.strip()`, and reassigns `auth_raw = token` before the final `_clean_secret(auth_raw).strip()` assembly. Whitespace-only bare strings now collapse to empty auth, matching the host_raw defense. The ordering (dict→unwrap→_clean_secret→strip) is correct and agent-type-agnostic.\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:608\",\n      \"issue\": \"NUL-only dict token bypasses validation: `not token.strip()` evaluates `not '\\\\x00'.strip()` → `not '\\\\x00'` → False (NUL is truthy after strip), so a token of pure NUL characters (e.g. `{'mode':'token','token':'\\\\x00'}`) passes validation but then `_clean_secret('\\\\x00').strip()` collapses it to empty string, silently producing a no-auth gateway instead of raising AgentConfigError.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Apply `_clean_secret` before the truthiness check to close the NUL-only gap: `token = _clean_secret(token)` then `if not isinstance(token, str) or not token.strip():`. This mirrors the bare-string path where `_clean_secret` runs first. Alternatively, validate with `not token.strip() or not _clean_secret(token).strip()` to cover both whitespace-only and NUL-only without changing the control flow.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:635\",\n      \"issue\": \"The `_clean_secret(auth_raw).strip()` pattern is correct but the defense is split across two calls with different semantics — `_clean_secret` removes NUL/CR/LF, `.strip()` removes whitespace. If someone later adds a new secret field and copies only `_clean_secret(x)` without `.strip()`, the whitespace-only defense is lost.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Consider extracting a helper `_clean_and_strip(value: str | None) -\u003e str` that applies both `_clean_secret` and `.strip()` in the correct order, documenting the invariant that both are always needed together for user-facing config fields. This reduces the chance of a future copy-paste omission.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Consider running `_clean_secret` before the dict-token truthiness check at line 608 to ensure NUL-only tokens are caught by validation rather than silently collapsing downstream.\",\n    \"All four prior blockers confirmed resolved: (1) dict auth no longer crashes _clean_secret, (2) missing token key raises AgentConfigError, (3) whitespace-only dict token raises AgentConfigError, (4) whitespace-only bare-string auth collapses to empty/no-auth block.\"\n  ],\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"files_reviewed\": 6,\n    \"domain\": \"render-engine\",\n    \"prior_blockers_resolved\": [\"R1-B1 dict crashes _clean_secret\", \"R1-B2 missing token key empty bearer\", \"R2-B1 whitespace-only dict token bypass\", \"R2-B2 whitespace-only bare-string no-auth gateway\"]\n  }\n}\n\u003c/output\u003e",
