    {
      "agent_id": "e8462619-249e-41f6-8cb0-a7169ae20d74",
      "agent_name": "security-reviewer",
      "status": "completed",
      "result": "\u003coutput\u003e\n{\n  \"rating\": 3,\n  \"summary\": \"The dict-shape unwrap and validation logic closes most of the auth-bypass holes flagged in review-2, and error messages do not leak token material. However, the validation checks the raw token value while the final auth is the cleaned-and-stripped value, leaving a residual bypass for NUL/CR/LF-only dict tokens that silently produces a no-auth gateway. The asymmetric treatment of whitespace between dict-shape (raises) and bare-string (silently empties) is also a defense-in-depth weakness that contradicts the stated #437 invariant.\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:606-613\",\n      \"issue\": \"Dict-shape NUL/CR/LF-only token bypasses the 'missing or empty token' validation. `token.strip()` removes only ASCII whitespace, not NUL/CR/LF — so `{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\", \\\"token\\\": \\\"\\\\x00\\\\x00\\\"}` (or `\\\"\\\\r\\\\n\\\\x00\\\"`) passes the validation as truthy, then is fed to `_clean_secret(auth_raw).strip()` on line 631, which collapses to `\\\"\\\"`. `_render_openclaw_json` then drops the auth block entirely (`if gateway.auth:` on line 1788) and emits an unauthenticated gateway config. The reviewer claim that 'every malformed dict raises' is therefore false for the NUL-only subset. None of the new dict-shape rejection tests cover this case; the only NUL test exercises an interior-NUL string that still has surviving bytes after cleaning.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Validate the cleaned form, not the raw form: `cleaned = _clean_secret(token).strip(); if not cleaned: raise AgentConfigError(...)`. Add a test like `({\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\", \\\"token\\\": \\\"\\\\x00\\\\x00\\\"}, \\\"missing or empty 'token'\\\")` to the `test_gateway_auth_rejects_malformed_shapes` parametrize block.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:631 and tests/core/test_render.py:test_gateway_auth_bare_string_whitespace_becomes_empty\",\n      \"issue\": \"Asymmetric whitespace handling: dict-shape `{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\", \\\"token\\\": \\\"   \\\"}` raises AgentConfigError, but bare-string `\\\"   \\\"` silently collapses to `\\\"\\\"` and produces a config with no `auth` block at all. Both inputs represent the same operator-visible failure class (corrupted/empty bearer in hosts.json) but the bare-string path is the WORSE outcome from an auth standpoint — the dict path errors loudly, while the bare-string path produces an unauthenticated gateway. The test explicitly pins this behavior (`assert '\\\"auth\\\"' not in json_body`) and the comment on line 624-632 frames it as 'matching the semantics of an absent auth key'. Under the stated #437 invariant ('every lifecycle op mints a fresh bearer'), an empty bearer at render time means the rotation either did not run or wrote garbage, and the renderer should fail loudly so the operator sees the broken state — not silently strip the auth requirement.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Either (a) raise `AgentConfigError` for whitespace-only bare-string auth, mirroring the dict path, OR (b) document explicitly in render.py that an empty bearer is the documented post-render representation of 'never paired' (which is currently only consistent with greenfield install before the first rotation, not with the #437 'always re-pair' model). Option (a) is the safer choice.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:579-619\",\n      \"issue\": \"The dict-shape unwrap accepts arbitrary extra keys (e.g. `{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\", \\\"token\\\": \\\"abc\\\", \\\"future_field\\\": \\\"x\\\"}` passes without comment). This is fine for forward compat but creates a silent-acceptance contract that future schema additions can rely on by accident. Not a security finding, but worth noting because the surrounding code is otherwise strict about shape.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Optional: if you want strict shape enforcement, validate the key set is exactly `{\\\"mode\\\", \\\"token\\\"}`. If you want forward compat (more likely), add a one-line comment noting that extra keys are intentionally permitted.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:1784-1793 (existing code; relevant to this review)\",\n      \"issue\": \"`_render_openclaw_json` drops the `auth` block when `gateway.auth` is empty (`if gateway.auth:` branch). Combined with the bare-string-whitespace collapse on line 631, this is the silent unauth path. Under the #437 model, configured openclaw agents must always have a bearer post-rotation; an empty bearer at this point is an invariant violation, not a valid state to render around.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Consider hard-failing in `_render_openclaw_json` if `gateway is not None and not gateway.auth` for openclaw — the caller (`lifecycle.configure_agent` / `sync_agent_canonical`) is supposed to have rotated the bearer before this code runs. Failing loudly here would close finding 2 as well.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Add NUL/CR/LF-only dict-token test cases to `test_gateway_auth_rejects_malformed_shapes` and change the dict-branch token check to validate `_clean_secret(token).strip()` so the validation gate and the final auth value use the same predicate.\",\n    \"Resolve the bare-string vs dict-shape whitespace asymmetry by raising in both cases — the #437 invariant is the security property the issue was opened to protect, and silent-empty bare-string undermines it.\",\n    \"No token material appears in error messages — keep that contract; do not add the raw token to any future error/log line.\",\n    \"Confirm with a follow-up test that `render_openclaw` raises (or otherwise fails loudly) when an openclaw agent record reaches the renderer with an empty bearer, so the #437 invariant is enforced at the last line of defense.\"\n  ],\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"files_reviewed\": 2,\n    \"domain\": \"security-reviewer\"\n  }\n}\n\u003c/output\u003e",
